Template: monero/rpc-port
Type: string
Default: 18081
Description: Port for RPC connections
 Set this to the port your local applications will use to access monerod.

Template: monero/p2p-port
Type: string
Default: 18080
Description: Port for peer-to-peer connections
 Set this to the port monerod will use to communicate with other nodes.

Template: monero/restricted-rpc
Type: boolean
Default: true
Description: Enable restricted RPC
 Restricts what commands can be run over RPC for external applications.

Template: monero/no-igd
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Disable UPnP IGD port forwarding
 Prevents monerod from attempting to automatically forward ports using UPnP.

Template: monero/disable-rpc-ban
Type: boolean
Default: false
Description: Disable automatic RPC IP banning
 Prevents IPs from being banned after issuing invalid RPC requests.

Template: monero/outpeers
Type: string
Default: 24
Description: Limit number of outgoing peers
 Optionally specify the maximum number of outgoing peer connections.

Template: monero/inpeers
Type: string
Default: 48
Description: Limit number of incoming peers
 Optionally specify the maximum number of incoming peer connections.

Template: monero/rpc-username
Type: string
Default: 
Description: RPC username
 Optional: Specify a username required for RPC connections.

Template: monero/rpc-password
Type: password
Default: 
Description: RPC password
 Optional: Specify a password to pair with the RPC username.
